      • addDisconnectedHandler

        void addDisconnectedHandler(ClientDisconnectedHandler clientDisconnectedHandler)
        Adds a Handler, that will be invoked once the Connection between the Server and the Client is terminated.

        Any Handler set, will be completely invoked if:

        • The Server calls Client.disconnect().
        • The internet-connection between the ServerStart and the ClientStart breaks.
        • Some IO-Exception is encountered within all Sockets of a active Connections
        Parameters:
        clientDisconnectedHandler - the Handler, that should be called once the Connection is terminated

      • startBlockerThread

        void startBlockerThread()
        Calling this Method is used to block the application from existing.

        By Default, NetCom2 utilizes mostly daemon Threads. This means, you could prepare a ClientStart and launch it, but the program exists right after the last statement.

        To counter this, the ClientStart provides 2 functions, this and the function blockOnCurrentThread().

        This Methods starts a new non-daemon Thread. This Thread will run, until an internal Synchronization mechanism is finished.

        This Thread may not be joined or interrupted, nor shut down forcefully.

        You can shut it down, using SoftStoppable.softStop().

        The Thread utilizes the method blockOnCurrentThread() and allows you to use the current Thread for different Tasks. On the other hand does this Method create a new Thread.

        See Also:
        blockOnCurrentThread(), SoftStoppable.softStop()

      • blockOnCurrentThread

        void blockOnCurrentThread()
        Calling this Method is used to block the application from existing.

        By Default, NetCom2 utilizes mostly daemon Threads. This means, you could prepare a ClientStart and launch it, but the program exists right after the last statement.

        To counter this, the ClientStart provides 2 functions, this and the function startBlockerThread().

        This Method synchronizes over an internally maintained Synchronize instance. This means, calling this Method will result in a block of the current Thread until SoftStoppable.softStop() is called and all dependencies are shut down.

        The absolute shutdown time is not known, but you may use this Method freely to synchronize your application.

        See Also:
        startBlockerThread(), SoftStoppable.softStop()
